I"ˆ<h1 id="potato-dauphinoise">Potato Dauphinoise</h1>
<h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1kg potatoes</li>
  <li>4 garlic cloves</li>
  <li>30g butter</li>
  <li>300 ml cream 30%</li>
  <li>Salt</li>
  <li>Pepper</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="method">Method</h1>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Pre heat the oven to 160Â°C.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Peel and thinly slice the potatoes into thin 2-3mm discs</li>
  <li>Spread the butter over the sides and base of on oven casserole (with fingers)</li>
  <li>Mince the garlic and sprinkle over the bottom</li>
  <li>Arrange a  layer of potatoes</li>
  <li>Generously season with salt and pepper</li>
  <li>Cover with another layer of potatoes</li>
  <li>Repeat seasoning and covering for layers 2,3 and 4</li>
  <li>Pour the cream all over the potatoes making sure they are all covered</li>
  <li>Place in the oven for 1h30, or until the top is brown and crispy.</li>
</ul>
